spanGrp.span: Those carrying the rife are hiding from the killers.
(_) Mõglö-wa tsã'bi je ñã blö-gẽ pe ñã ktö-gẽ yiga
It seems that they do not want to go.
It seems that they do not want to go.
kuẽĩ jeska í kajali jeyikwö bö anẽtsö nara
they are big and they see them, open them and see through them.
Je rö blibli sũẽ-gẽ-ite juyukwö köye-gẽ-ite bi Je nẽ sũẽ-gẽ-ite sũẽ-gẽ-ite
They hide and eat right there;
jemẽ (m) í wakwa ñã blö-gẽ jeska böi í wakwa yökö-gẽ
it seems that they are hiding inside a hole where no one can see them.
Jebi juela í jalali ñã ble-lë-wã rö kã' kã' blajãrga ka yurö të sũẽ ska
There they were crowded together, so it seems.
Jeska í jalali ñã wötiá juela rö tã'ĩ
There they were crowded together, so it seems.
There they eat, but they do not go out;
Jeska í yökö-gate tara ka í ñãyusã'
There they eat, but they do not go out;
Juela tã'ĩ (_) ñã ble-lë-nẽ rö kal digijãrga
But as one of them threw something, it fell on another one’s hand/side.
ta jiröwa e-gla të jirö jũã'-nẽ (_) janã-mĩ-nẽ e-gla jula/ e-gla kã'ga-nẽ
So, he hit him on the face right away with something sticky.
Je të e-gla tiá í wö inga egwetanẽ dabájanẽ
¿ta ñera jirö í rö e nã
It is impossible to see whether it is something liquid or solid.
Ñera ka í juela ta diuga í rö ta jirö shtö í rö í (_) yagaga í rö inga (m)
It hit him right on his face.
Ta je të e-gla bö tiá plaja í wö jãrga
ñerö jeska bönẽ jeska bönẽ í õnã'-wã
but it is not possible to see what it is, or why they are hiding.’
Tara ka ka í juer böi nã jirö í rö inga (m) jiröwa í tsõ ñã ble-lë ka je juer
